profile_positions.description:
Topaz Energy and Marine is a leading offshore support vessel (“OSV”) company providing marine solutions to the global energy industry with primary focus on the Caspian, Middle East, West Africa and Subsea operations in the North Sea and Gulf of Mexico. Headquartered in Dubai with 40 years of experience in the Middle East, Topaz operates a fleet of more than 90 offshore support vessels of an average age of 7 years, well below the global average of 15 years. 

Role: HR Generalist function from transactional and strategic HR point of view, supporting various HR functions for UAE, KSA, Qatar, Norway, Vietnam, Romania, Africa, Russia, Kazakhstan, Azerbaijan, Turkmenistan regions (+400 onshore staff).
- Played an instrumental role in overall achievement of Group vision in an efficient manner and in compliance with local legislation.
-  Demonstrated success by adding value to HR processes by developing and implementing corporate policies and procedures.
- Partnered with (Senior) management to help the business to achieve its goals and assess the impact of business decision on all HR aspects;
- Was involved in recruitment of onshore staff of all levels;
- Revised, developed and implemented HR Policies and Procedures
- Administrated Expat Staff Payroll (+200 onshore stuff in various regions);
- Oversaw employee on boarding and off boarding procedures.

Miclyn Express Offshore (MEO) is a leading provider of service vessels to the expanding offshore oil and gas industry across South-East Asia, Australia and the Middle East. The company is headquartered in Singapore and has been operating through its predecessor entities since the 1970s.

Role: HR & Crew Payroll Executive, responsible for organizing and coordinating office operations and procedures, services and efficiency, supervising office staff and maintaining office records, in order to ensure organizational effectiveness; as well as crew planning, payroll and recruitment.

Reported directly to Head of Business Unit – Middle East.
- Identified as an emerging Talent within the organization - a Program set up and initiated by the CEO of Miclyn Express Offshore.
- Awarded the “Multitasker Award” at Miclyn Express Offshore;
- Administrated payroll (+350 Expat Crew Members);
- Was involved in recruitment of offshore and onshore staff at various levels;
- Contributed to the development of Company Policies andProcedures;
- Analyzed, monitored the appliance of UAE, Saudi Arabia, Qatar Labor law;
- Planned external & internal training overview and events based onidentified training needs.
- Revised and developed job descriptions for +100 onshore staff;
- Was a focal point to staff grievances and complaints;
- Administrated the induction and end of service processes.

Role: Procurement specialist in charge of managing initial procurement activities for 5 construction projects for the Government of Abu Dhabi.
- Ensured the efficient provision of materials for all construction phases of the project;
- Created a new database of products with product references to provide clients with faster and more transparent solutions;
- Spearheaded the creation and implementation of more stringent procedures around purchase order and invoicing processes for recurring services to ensure more accurate budgeting for the Finance Department.

Part time Job while studying as Assistant Professor of the course «Development of private international law».
- Created a new resource library for all course materials and edited and updated the course material;
- Received praise for streamlining the teaching schedule to facilitate both lecturers and student schedules.
